                "name": "Shaunak Bhattachharje",
                "href": "/profile/Shaunak-Bhattachharje"
            },
            "answer_text": "Earning 1.2 lakh rupees a year is way below market standards. These service based companies like Infosys, Cognizant that you mentioned offer between Rs 3.5\u20134 lakh rupees to freshers. After one year experience, they earn around 3.8 to 4.2 lakh rupees annually.  So when you switch to these companies, ask for 4 lakh rupees minimum. Tell them that you are okay with the salary which they offer to employees with similar roles. Start with asking for Rs 4.5 lakh showing your experience and skill set. If you can negotiate well, they can settle between Rs 4\u20134.5 lakh or else you should get 4 lakh minimum from the experience that you hold. That would still be a 233% hike which is great.  Good luck on your job switch! ",
